WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:32.532 --> 00:00:36.119 position:50% align:center
Yakumo... Sumeragi?

00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:52.844 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:52.927 --> 00:00:54.220 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Karen.

00:00:54.304 --> 00:00:57.182 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
So, you're the same person?

00:00:57.265 --> 00:00:59.017 position:50% align:center
I just don't believe it.

00:01:00.435 --> 00:01:04.981 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] What is this?
Something's not right.

00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:10.070 position:50% align:center
♪

00:02:39.409 --> 00:02:43.329 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
No. It wasn't like this before.

00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:45.373 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:02:45.457 --> 00:02:47.125 position:50% align:center
Karen.

00:02:47.208 --> 00:02:51.421 position:50% align:center
You've really been down
here for 2,000 years.

00:02:51.504 --> 00:02:52.922 position:50% align:center
Is that true?

00:02:53.006 --> 00:02:57.177 position:50% align:center
Karen. There's something that
we need you to do for us.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:00.764 position:50% align:center
Help us destroy the Kunad Gate,
or the world will end!

00:03:04.726 --> 00:03:06.936 position:50% align:center
When you traveled through time,

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:09.981 position:50% align:center
by using Arahabaki
and the Red Strings,

00:03:10.065 --> 00:03:12.025 position:50% align:center
you decided to interfere
with events that happened

00:03:12.108 --> 00:03:16.780 position:50% align:center
2,000 years ago that
created an entanglement.

00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:20.533 position:50% align:center
Unless we rectify it,
the Gate will remain.

00:03:20.617 --> 00:03:25.413 position:50% align:center
She's right. If we don't do
something, humanity will perish!

00:03:25.497 --> 00:03:27.540 position:50% align:center
So please, we need your help!

00:03:27.624 --> 00:03:29.417 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
It won't solve anything.

00:03:29.501 --> 00:03:32.128 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]
But the person who creates

00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:35.924 position:50% align:center
a dimensional entanglement is
the one who has to unravel it.

00:03:36.007 --> 00:03:38.677 position:50% align:center
We know because we've
done it ourselves!

00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:39.928 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
I realize that.

00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.846 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Are you kidding me?

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:43.807 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Then why won't you help?

00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:45.642 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
Because it won't do any good.

00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:48.144 position:50% align:center
That's the truth of it.

00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:49.062 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:03:49.145 --> 00:03:50.689 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:03:51.398 --> 00:03:52.816 position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

00:03:52.899 --> 00:03:55.235 position:50% align:center
Wait. This doesn't add up.

00:03:55.318 --> 00:03:58.988 position:50% align:center
You moved through time in
the hope of saving Alice.

00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:02.158 position:50% align:center
But why go back 2,000 years?

00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:06.037 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] I didn't understand,
not at first.

00:04:06.121 --> 00:04:07.372 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
At first?

00:04:07.455 --> 00:04:10.917 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] As you are aware,
Yakumo Sumeragi was born

00:04:11.001 --> 00:04:15.588 position:50% align:center
a Red Strings-user, and I
believe that I must have been

00:04:15.672 --> 00:04:18.008 position:50% align:center
drawn to that power somehow.

00:04:18.091 --> 00:04:20.677 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI] So, you casually
jumped two millennia?

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:24.097 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] I was searching,
hoping there was a way

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:29.519 position:50% align:center
to change the future so that
we'd meet in our own time.

00:04:29.602 --> 00:04:32.313 position:50% align:center
And you thought that the
solution was to become

00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:34.274 position:50% align:center
Yakumo Sumeragi?

00:04:34.357 --> 00:04:36.860 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] I was certain that the
office of the nation's founder

00:04:36.943 --> 00:04:39.988 position:50% align:center
would prove itself
useful to my cause.

00:04:40.071 --> 00:04:42.323 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Useful? What did you plan to do?

00:04:42.407 --> 00:04:44.576 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
Many ages after that,

00:04:44.659 --> 00:04:48.496 position:50% align:center
I discovered the only way that
I could hope to save Alice.

00:04:49.873 --> 00:04:52.876 position:50% align:center
What did you do? Tell us.

00:04:52.959 --> 00:04:54.210 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
It was simple.

00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:57.172 position:50% align:center
I connected myself to Arahabaki.

00:04:58.923 --> 00:05:01.092 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:05:05.055 --> 00:05:07.015 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] I thought that
if my brain was synced up

00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:10.060 position:50% align:center
with the heart of
all other systems,

00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:14.439 position:50% align:center
I could change history
and rescue Alice.

00:05:14.522 --> 00:05:15.815 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:15.899 --> 00:05:17.400 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI]
This is crazy.

00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:21.988 position:50% align:center
A bio-computer that uses your
brain in tandem with Arahabaki?

00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:24.908 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] So, all those
intrusions into our brains,

00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:27.035 position:50% align:center
they were because of you?

00:05:27.118 --> 00:05:28.745 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
This doesn't add up.

00:05:28.828 --> 00:05:32.624 position:50% align:center
After everything you did,
why didn't she come back?

00:05:32.707 --> 00:05:35.669 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] I don't know.
I tried so many times.

00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:38.129 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:38.213 --> 00:05:40.215 position:50% align:center
How many?

00:05:40.298 --> 00:05:42.509 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] I've sent
countless copies of myself

00:05:42.592 --> 00:05:47.138 position:50% align:center
throughout time, in hopes
of taking Yakumo's place.

00:05:47.222 --> 00:05:48.640 position:50% align:center
And what does that mean?

00:05:48.723 --> 00:05:50.350 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
Dimensional entanglements occur

00:05:50.433 --> 00:05:51.810 position:50% align:center
in each instance.

00:05:51.893 --> 00:05:56.022 position:50% align:center
But if I try to unravel them,
then I can't rescue her.

00:05:56.106 --> 00:05:57.982 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:05:58.066 --> 00:06:00.402 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Yes, that's exactly right.

00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:03.530 position:50% align:center
I create new dimensional
entanglements.

00:06:03.613 --> 00:06:04.489 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:06:04.572 --> 00:06:05.573 position:50% align:center
Brother!

00:06:05.657 --> 00:06:07.784 position:50% align:center
They're both Karen?

00:06:07.867 --> 00:06:09.327 position:50% align:center
What is this?

00:06:09.411 --> 00:06:12.455 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
It's you. I don't understand.

00:06:12.539 --> 00:06:15.041 position:50% align:center
What are you doing here?

00:06:15.125 --> 00:06:18.878 position:50% align:center
I'll be asking the questions!
Now explain this;

00:06:18.962 --> 00:06:22.257 position:50% align:center
You told me to become
Yakumo and link to Arahabaki.

00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:25.927 position:50% align:center
That nothing else would be
enough to save Alice's life!

00:06:26.011 --> 00:06:28.888 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] It's true,
that's the only way.

00:06:28.972 --> 00:06:31.307 position:50% align:center
You must travel through time.

00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:33.685 position:50% align:center
The proof is stored
on Arahabaki.

00:06:33.768 --> 00:06:36.062 position:50% align:center
It kept records of
every single attempt,

00:06:36.146 --> 00:06:37.897 position:50% align:center
from the very beginning.

00:06:37.981 --> 00:06:40.817 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] Then why can't
I go back 2,000 years?

00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:42.152 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
What do you mean?

00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:44.446 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] Why have I failed
to travel through time?

00:06:44.529 --> 00:06:46.448 position:50% align:center
Answer me!

00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:49.284 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
Did I not help you?

00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:51.619 position:50% align:center
It was you.

00:06:51.703 --> 00:06:52.912 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh?

00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:56.833 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Tell me everything you know,

00:06:56.916 --> 00:06:58.585 position:50% align:center
or I'll destroy you
here and now!

00:06:58.668 --> 00:06:59.878 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:07:01.296 --> 00:07:05.216 position:50% align:center
Start talking or else your
entire memory will be mine!

00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:10.305 position:50% align:center
[KAREN, YAKUMO yell]

00:07:14.809 --> 00:07:16.478 position:50% align:center
[ALL grunt]

00:07:16.561 --> 00:07:20.440 position:50% align:center
[KAREN grunts]

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:33.787 position:50% align:center
[HANABI gasps]
He absorbed all of him?

00:07:36.247 --> 00:07:39.292 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:39.376 --> 00:07:43.380 position:50% align:center
Finally, my brain's
connected to Arahabaki,

00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:45.882 position:50% align:center
it's such a powerful sensation!

00:07:45.965 --> 00:07:50.095 position:50% align:center
All of the data it holds
now belongs to me!

00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:50.929 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
No way!

00:07:51.012 --> 00:07:52.263 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
For real?

00:07:52.347 --> 00:07:54.766 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA] You can see
everything inside Arahabaki?

00:07:54.849 --> 00:07:59.854 position:50% align:center
[KAREN laughs]

00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:14.202 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
What the hell's happening?

00:08:19.416 --> 00:08:22.252 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:08:26.673 --> 00:08:30.593 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:08:33.763 --> 00:08:36.224 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
The truth is, you know nothing.

00:08:36.307 --> 00:08:37.934 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
How dare you!

00:08:38.018 --> 00:08:41.396 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] Try as you might,
that will never change.

00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:44.524 position:50% align:center
You will always be an
infinitesimal fraction

00:08:44.607 --> 00:08:46.192 position:50% align:center
of what I am.

00:08:46.276 --> 00:08:47.861 position:50% align:center
You might as well give up now.

00:08:47.944 --> 00:08:49.154 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Huh?

00:08:57.078 --> 00:08:59.080 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO]
How many attempts?

00:08:59.164 --> 00:09:01.791 position:50% align:center
How many times have
I transferred the data

00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:05.045 position:50% align:center
to my countless copies?

00:09:05.128 --> 00:09:09.382 position:50% align:center
And yet, the future
remains unaffected.

00:09:09.466 --> 00:09:12.385 position:50% align:center
Alice can't be saved.

00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:15.305 position:50% align:center
I have observed
every single try,

00:09:15.388 --> 00:09:19.976 position:50% align:center
and I am the only one who
could've changed things.

00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:23.605 position:50% align:center
You have struggled endlessly,
and predictably,

00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:25.982 position:50% align:center
you have nothing to show for it.

00:09:26.066 --> 00:09:31.154 position:50% align:center
Lest you forget, you are but one
individual among the infinite.

00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:34.699 position:50% align:center
That's enough! It's a lie!

00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:37.160 position:50% align:center
Shut your mouth!

00:09:37.243 --> 00:09:39.579 position:50% align:center
I won't be stopped!

00:09:39.662 --> 00:09:41.206 position:50% align:center
I'll try every way possible,

00:09:41.289 --> 00:09:43.667 position:50% align:center
and I don't care how
many times it takes me!

00:09:43.750 --> 00:09:44.626 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:09:44.709 --> 00:09:46.169 position:50% align:center
Damn you two!

00:09:46.252 --> 00:09:48.380 position:50% align:center
Surrender your
Red Strings to me!

00:09:48.463 --> 00:09:50.298 position:50% align:center
[LUKA, ARASHI grunt]

00:09:54.177 --> 00:09:56.596 position:50% align:center
You never got to
absorb Yuito's skill.

00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:57.764 position:50% align:center
That must've been the reason

00:09:57.847 --> 00:09:59.766 position:50% align:center
you weren't able to
travel through time!

00:09:59.849 --> 00:10:01.726 position:50% align:center
I think I understand now.

00:10:01.810 --> 00:10:03.478 position:50% align:center
You can't sustain
the Red Strings,

00:10:03.561 --> 00:10:05.563 position:50% align:center
so you keep on copying it!

00:10:05.647 --> 00:10:07.023 position:50% align:center
You're not strong enough!

00:10:07.107 --> 00:10:09.484 position:50% align:center
Don't waste your time resisting.

00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:12.987 position:50% align:center
I won't rest until I harness
the power of the Red Strings!

00:10:13.071 --> 00:10:17.117 position:50% align:center
Karen! If you time-travel now,
then the world will end!

00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:18.910 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Why should that matter?

00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:23.373 position:50% align:center
Because if I can't protect
Alice, let it be destroyed!

00:10:23.456 --> 00:10:25.792 position:50% align:center
Brother...

00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:29.087 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] So... you don't
intend to help us.

00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:30.880 position:50% align:center
Listen to me, Karen!

00:10:30.964 --> 00:10:33.717 position:50% align:center
Our society... The moon...

00:10:33.800 --> 00:10:35.343 position:50% align:center
There are lots of problems.

00:10:35.427 --> 00:10:38.513 position:50% align:center
But if the world ends,
then nothing will get solved!

00:10:38.596 --> 00:10:41.599 position:50% align:center
Our only choice is to
forge a new future!

00:10:41.683 --> 00:10:45.729 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] A world with such a
hideous past isn't worth saving.

00:10:45.812 --> 00:10:47.814 position:50% align:center
That's why I'm going
to modify history

00:10:47.897 --> 00:10:50.150 position:50% align:center
and set everything right again!

00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:53.653 position:50% align:center
I understand how badly you
want to save Alice, but...

00:10:53.737 --> 00:11:00.910 position:50% align:center
You don't, at all and
I don't need you to!

00:11:02.954 --> 00:11:05.081 position:50% align:center
His power's growing
by the second!

00:11:05.165 --> 00:11:06.374 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI grunts]

00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:09.753 position:50% align:center
[LUKA grunts]

00:11:09.836 --> 00:11:10.795 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN, TSUGUMI grunt]

00:11:10.879 --> 00:11:12.088 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA, HANABI grunt]

00:11:14.132 --> 00:11:15.342 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:11:25.268 --> 00:11:26.770 position:50% align:center
Where'd they go?

00:11:34.819 --> 00:11:35.820 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO grunt]

00:11:35.904 --> 00:11:37.864 position:50% align:center
Think of the ones you hold dear.

00:11:37.947 --> 00:11:39.240 position:50% align:center
Could you let them go?

00:11:39.324 --> 00:11:40.784 position:50% align:center
Even to save the world?

00:11:40.867 --> 00:11:43.578 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:11:43.661 --> 00:11:46.706 position:50% align:center
[NAGI] After intense
and varied training,

00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:49.250 position:50% align:center
these two have become
Scarlet Guardians,

00:11:49.334 --> 00:11:53.004 position:50% align:center
the courageous warriors who
protect our planet from danger.

00:11:55.048 --> 00:11:56.466 position:50% align:center
Nagi.

00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:59.552 position:50% align:center
Private First Class
Sumeragi and, of course,

00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:02.472 position:50% align:center
Private First Class Nagi Karman!

00:12:02.555 --> 00:12:03.807 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:03.890 --> 00:12:07.727 position:50% align:center
Good morning!
It's nice weather today.

00:12:07.811 --> 00:12:09.437 position:50% align:center
Naomi...

00:12:11.523 --> 00:12:13.358 position:50% align:center
This'll be perfect!

00:12:13.441 --> 00:12:14.859 position:50% align:center
Your dream came true!

00:12:14.943 --> 00:12:16.653 position:50% align:center
It's what you've wanted
since you were a kid,

00:12:16.736 --> 00:12:18.238 position:50% align:center
so don't let anything stop you!

00:12:18.321 --> 00:12:20.865 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:12:20.949 --> 00:12:22.283 position:50% align:center
[NAGI grunts]

00:12:22.367 --> 00:12:23.952 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:12:24.035 --> 00:12:28.164 position:50% align:center
Why don't we go out?
I know, let's get Baki charms!

00:12:28.248 --> 00:12:29.290 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:31.042 position:50% align:center
Wait!

00:12:31.126 --> 00:12:33.003 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
Hey, Yuito.

00:12:33.086 --> 00:12:36.047 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] I know you
want to, Kasane. Please?

00:12:36.131 --> 00:12:39.884 position:50% align:center
You care about me, don't you?
Come back to the past, okay?

00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:42.220 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
I need you to help me, sis.

00:12:59.404 --> 00:13:02.699 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI growls]

00:13:02.782 --> 00:13:04.242 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
I know you can do it.

00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:08.246 position:50% align:center
What do you say, Yuito?
You up to the task?

00:13:08.329 --> 00:13:12.751 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] I know you have regrets,
don't you, Kasane?

00:13:12.834 --> 00:13:16.004 position:50% align:center
If you had only realized
in that brief moment,

00:13:16.087 --> 00:13:18.923 position:50% align:center
that something
wasn't quite right...

00:13:19.007 --> 00:13:21.926 position:50% align:center
...then, I'd be safe.

00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:23.219 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:26.097 --> 00:13:28.725 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] I wouldn't have
been turned into a monster!

00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:34.356 position:50% align:center
Don't you feel guilty?
If only you'd done something.

00:13:34.439 --> 00:13:36.358 position:50% align:center
Have you heard from Nagi?

00:13:36.441 --> 00:13:39.652 position:50% align:center
He was sent to the hospital,
and then nothing.

00:13:39.736 --> 00:13:44.449 position:50% align:center
[NAGI] If you had come to
find me, I would've survived.

00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:48.495 position:50% align:center
Weird. I don't know
what's going on.

00:13:48.578 --> 00:13:51.915 position:50% align:center
A voice is telling
me to kill you.

00:13:51.998 --> 00:13:56.670 position:50% align:center
But why? I don't want to fight,
but it makes me!

00:13:56.753 --> 00:13:59.839 position:50% align:center
I can't stop it.
I'm really scared.

00:13:59.923 --> 00:14:02.384 position:50% align:center
I regret it. I do.

00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:04.844 position:50% align:center
Even if I'd made slightly
different choices,

00:14:04.928 --> 00:14:10.517 position:50% align:center
then maybe the outcome would've
changed completely, but still!

00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:14.646 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] In each moment,
you make one choice or another!

00:14:14.729 --> 00:14:15.939 position:50% align:center
That's just life!

00:14:16.022 --> 00:14:19.734 position:50% align:center
We decide things and
move forward! We have to!

00:14:19.818 --> 00:14:22.696 position:50% align:center
So, we try to do
the right thing!

00:14:22.779 --> 00:14:24.906 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI growls]

00:14:27.575 --> 00:14:28.910 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
Hmph.

00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:36.001 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, KASANE gasp]

00:14:36.084 --> 00:14:37.419 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
The way I see it,

00:14:37.502 --> 00:14:40.046 position:50% align:center
you protected those people
until it served you better

00:14:40.130 --> 00:14:41.381 position:50% align:center
to let them go.

00:14:41.464 --> 00:14:45.051 position:50% align:center
You only cared about them
up to a certain point.

00:14:45.135 --> 00:14:47.804 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] No! It's more
complicated than that!

00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:49.806 position:50% align:center
This proves that I am
nothing like you!

00:14:49.889 --> 00:14:52.267 position:50% align:center
He was always by my side!

00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:54.436 position:50% align:center
What happened to
him was terrible.

00:14:54.519 --> 00:14:57.522 position:50% align:center
Even so, I have to accept
the truth for what it is!

00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:59.691 position:50% align:center
That's what losing
him has taught me!

00:14:59.774 --> 00:15:03.778 position:50% align:center
All we can do is face the future
and leave the past behind,

00:15:03.862 --> 00:15:05.697 position:50% align:center
not keep trying to change it!

00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:08.742 position:50% align:center
You're both pathetic!
You think you're being brave,

00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:12.537 position:50% align:center
but that's an excuse to avert
your eyes and run from tragedy!

00:15:12.620 --> 00:15:13.830 position:50% align:center
Well, I won't run.

00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:16.207 position:50% align:center
I'll save Alice,
whatever it takes!

00:15:16.291 --> 00:15:17.667 position:50% align:center
Just listen to me!

00:15:17.751 --> 00:15:19.377 position:50% align:center
Looking back in your memories,

00:15:19.461 --> 00:15:21.421 position:50% align:center
didn't she give you
hope for the future?

00:15:21.504 --> 00:15:23.089 position:50% align:center
To move forward and grow?

00:15:23.173 --> 00:15:24.090 position:50% align:center
What?

00:15:24.174 --> 00:15:25.675 position:50% align:center
Just think about it!

00:15:25.759 --> 00:15:27.260 position:50% align:center
Look, be honest.

00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:28.636 position:50% align:center
If it meant the
end of the world,

00:15:28.720 --> 00:15:30.221 position:50% align:center
wouldn't she tell
you to back down--?

00:15:30.305 --> 00:15:32.057 position:50% align:center
Stop talking like
you know her!

00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:34.434 position:50% align:center
You're connected
to Arahabaki now,

00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:36.853 position:50% align:center
so that means you
must understand!

00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:38.646 position:50% align:center
And you know how Alice feels!

00:15:38.730 --> 00:15:39.898 position:50% align:center
That's enough!

00:15:39.981 --> 00:15:43.318 position:50% align:center
Even if the whole world
plunges into chaos,

00:15:43.401 --> 00:15:45.487 position:50% align:center
I will never change my mind!

00:15:50.575 --> 00:15:52.827 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
I've decided!

00:15:52.911 --> 00:15:54.704 position:50% align:center
That's it!

00:15:54.788 --> 00:15:56.539 position:50% align:center
I won't stop!

00:15:57.582 --> 00:16:02.545 position:50% align:center
Give it to me! Your Red
Strings power is mine!

00:16:04.339 --> 00:16:07.342 position:50% align:center
Let's do it, Kasane!

00:16:07.425 --> 00:16:09.511 position:50% align:center
After I've taken your
ability from you,

00:16:09.594 --> 00:16:11.763 position:50% align:center
you'll be completely
useless to me!

00:16:11.846 --> 00:16:14.891 position:50% align:center
Alright! I think it's time
we fight fire with fire!

00:16:14.974 --> 00:16:16.017 position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

00:16:16.101 --> 00:16:17.435 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, KASANE grunt]

00:16:19.896 --> 00:16:21.147 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
What the--? 

00:16:21.231 --> 00:16:25.026 position:50% align:center
[KAREN shouts]

00:16:41.042 --> 00:16:42.627 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] We're scouring
Arahabaki's memories

00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:45.255 position:50% align:center
to find out who
Alice really was!

00:16:46.965 --> 00:16:48.967 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
She was a wonderful person.

00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:50.218 position:50% align:center
Anyone could see that,

00:16:50.301 --> 00:16:52.637 position:50% align:center
based on how determined
you are to protect her.

00:17:01.062 --> 00:17:02.063 position:50% align:center
Alice?

00:17:02.147 --> 00:17:04.566 position:50% align:center
[ALICE gasps]
Oh, thank you.

00:17:04.649 --> 00:17:06.818 position:50% align:center
What is it?

00:17:06.901 --> 00:17:12.949 position:50% align:center
It's just that... Karen's
constantly coming to my rescue.

00:17:13.033 --> 00:17:17.120 position:50% align:center
But today, he was
injured because of me.

00:17:17.203 --> 00:17:19.914 position:50% align:center
And it was a lot more than
a "scratch," like he said.

00:17:19.998 --> 00:17:21.666 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
That's the way he is.

00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:26.379 position:50% align:center
Except that I never asked
him to look out for me.

00:17:26.463 --> 00:17:31.343 position:50% align:center
To be honest, I just wish
he'd care more about himself.

00:17:31.426 --> 00:17:32.844 position:50% align:center
Me, too.

00:17:32.927 --> 00:17:34.179 position:50% align:center
[ALICE sighs]

00:17:41.895 --> 00:17:43.104 position:50% align:center
I...

00:17:46.191 --> 00:17:49.903 position:50% align:center
I would be crushed
if I lost him,

00:17:49.986 --> 00:17:52.864 position:50% align:center
which means I have to
get my act together.

00:17:52.947 --> 00:17:55.533 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Even if you do,

00:17:55.617 --> 00:17:58.495 position:50% align:center
it still won't make him
any less protective of you.

00:17:58.578 --> 00:18:00.038 position:50% align:center
You're right.

00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:05.126 position:50% align:center
That's all the more reason
for me to improve.

00:18:11.049 --> 00:18:15.303 position:50% align:center
[ALICE] I don't want Karen
to always worry about me,

00:18:15.387 --> 00:18:17.389 position:50% align:center
so I'll work harder.

00:18:17.472 --> 00:18:19.391 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Huh?

00:18:19.474 --> 00:18:23.019 position:50% align:center
[ALICE] All I want is
for him to be happy.

00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:29.401 position:50% align:center
[YAKUMO] Karen Travers.
How are you feeling now?

00:18:29.484 --> 00:18:31.778 position:50% align:center
Are you happy?

00:18:46.126 --> 00:18:48.294 position:50% align:center
No. Alice.

00:18:48.378 --> 00:18:49.796 position:50% align:center
Alice...

00:18:52.632 --> 00:18:55.677 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:19:09.315 --> 00:19:12.402 position:50% align:center
So, is that the end of it?

00:19:12.485 --> 00:19:14.487 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Yeah.

00:19:14.571 --> 00:19:18.033 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
No. This is wrong.

00:19:20.201 --> 00:19:21.036 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:21.119 --> 00:19:23.329 position:50% align:center
I refuse to accept it!

00:19:23.413 --> 00:19:27.000 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:29.878 position:50% align:center
I will not let it end this way!

00:19:29.961 --> 00:19:30.837 position:50% align:center
Brother!

00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:33.340 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:38.428 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:44.351 position:50% align:center
Yuito!

00:19:44.434 --> 00:19:45.685 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN, KYOKA, KAGERO gasp]

00:19:49.022 --> 00:19:52.359 position:50% align:center
[KAREN laughs]
That's it.

00:19:52.442 --> 00:19:55.779 position:50% align:center
I've finally copied
your Red Strings.

00:19:55.862 --> 00:19:58.365 position:50% align:center
Which means this
time I will not fail!

00:20:03.036 --> 00:20:07.957 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts] Karen, you saw
it with your own eyes.

00:20:08.041 --> 00:20:11.336 position:50% align:center
So you know what Alice's
true feelings are now!

00:20:11.419 --> 00:20:14.964 position:50% align:center
Alice, I'm coming to rescue you.

00:20:15.048 --> 00:20:16.424 position:50% align:center
Please wait for me.

00:20:16.508 --> 00:20:19.803 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:20:19.886 --> 00:20:21.096 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:20:21.179 --> 00:20:24.516 position:50% align:center
[KAREN grunts]

00:20:24.599 --> 00:20:27.602 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
I refuse to give up.

00:20:27.686 --> 00:20:30.480 position:50% align:center
This time will be different.

00:20:30.563 --> 00:20:33.149 position:50% align:center
I won't fail to save her life!

00:20:35.110 --> 00:20:36.945 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
He's too far gone.

00:20:43.326 --> 00:20:45.495 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:20:54.004 --> 00:20:54.879 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Well?

00:20:54.963 --> 00:20:57.215 position:50% align:center
Yeah. He's forced our hand.

00:21:12.313 --> 00:21:13.523 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:21:17.152 --> 00:21:21.072 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:21:29.581 --> 00:21:34.294 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:21:34.502 --> 00:21:35.503 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, KASANE]
Karen!

00:21:35.587 --> 00:21:36.796 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:43.595 --> 00:21:46.598 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:21:59.235 --> 00:22:04.240 position:50% align:center
[grunts, shouts]

00:22:15.335 --> 00:22:16.920 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:22:17.003 --> 00:22:18.588 position:50% align:center
[KAREN grunts]

00:22:27.722 --> 00:22:32.727 position:50% align:center
♪